result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob D Hagemann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:39 Defendant Jacob D Hagemann in court.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court questions defendant regarding non-representation. Defendant asks Court to appoint counsel. Court denies request to appoint counsel based on Affidavit of Indigency. Court will proceed with preliminary hearing today. 
David Drinkwine is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Lambert. He is a sergeant with the Grant Rapids Police Department. On 7/11/15, he observed the defendant driving a motor vehicle and it crossed over into the opposite lane twice. He stopped the vehicle. He observed THC in the vehicle. He found baggies of green, leafy substance in the vehicle, along with an open container. The substance tested positive for THC. He also observed another substance mixed with the THC. That substance tested positive for methamphetamines. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. 
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bound over for further proceedings. Bond is continued.  Arraignment scheduled for October 5, 2015 at 09:00 am.
